Table:JobDistance
Type:Lookup
Roll: 1d20
1-9: Local
10-15: Area
16-19: Distant ([@PickMegahex])
20: Very Distant ([@PickMegahex])

Table:LongerJobDistance      
Type:Lookup
Roll: 1d20
1-2: Local
3-5: Area
6-15: Distant ([@PickMegahex])
16-20: Very Distant ([@PickMegahex])

Table:JobTwistCheck
Type:Lookup
Roll: 1d10
;use for non-crim jobs
1-9: \z
10: \n [@JobTwist]

Table:JobTwist
\n <b>Twist</b>: Actual patron is nonhuman or monster \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Contractor intended as bait \n
\n &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <b>Twist</b>: Betrayal/delivery to player enemy \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Betrayal/delivery to employer enemy \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Betrayal/delivery to third party \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Patron not authorized to offer job \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job is something patron has been forbidden to do \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job is con or swindle \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job is doublecross or trap \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is being framed/set up \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Purported patron is actually agent for real patron \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about their motive \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about the reward \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about the job target \n 
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about the job target's allegiance or identity
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about the consequences \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about their allegiance \n 
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about success conditions \n 
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about necessary requirements \n 
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about their role or standing \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about job difficulty \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about job danger \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about likely consequences \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about job target \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about other contractors \n 
\n <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about the interested part(ies) \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Job target warned or alerted somehow \n
\n <b>Twist</b>: Third party will intervene vs. PCs \n

Table: JobPay
Type:Lookup
Roll: 1d10
1-3: \n <b>Pay</b>: Low {{1d3}*10} gp /job level) [|apiece|apiece|apiece|total]
4-7: \n <b>Pay</b>: Average ({{1d3}*100} gp/job level) [|apiece|apiece|apiece|total]
8-9: \n <b>Pay</b>: High (500 gp/job level) [|apiece|apiece|apiece|apiece|total]
10: \n <b>Pay</b>: Munificent (1000 gp/job level) [|apiece|apiece|apiece|apiece|apiece|total]

