Table:MageTwistCheck
Type:Lookup
Roll: 1d100
01-85: \z
86-100: [@MageTwist]

Table:MageTwist
Type:Lookup
Roll: 1d20
1: \n  <b>Twist</b>: Actual patron is nonhuman or monster
2: \n  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<b>Twist</b>: Contractor intended as bait
3: \n <b>Twist</b>: Betrayal/delivery to player enemy
4: \n <b>Twist</b>: Betrayal/delivery to employer enemy
5-6:\n  <b>Twist</b>: Job is something patron has been forbidden to do
7-8: \n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about their motive
9: \n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about the job target 
10: \n <b>Twist</b>: Job patron is lying about the consequences
11: \n <b>Twist</b>: Third party will intervene vs. PCs
12-13: \n <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about job difficulty
14-15: \n <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about job danger
16: \n <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about likely consequences
17: \n <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about job target
18: \n <b>Twist</b>: Doing job will have magical/curse effect
19: \n <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about other contractors 
20: \n  <b>Twist</b>: Crucial detail omitted about the interested part(ies)

Table:MagePay
Type:Lookup
Roll: 1d100
;idea is, they are richer, offer more special rewards, often want the real goodies though
01-06: \n  <b>Pay</b>: Low ({1d3}*10) gp./job level) &
 [|apiece|apiece|apiece|total]
07-11: \n <b>Pay</b>: Low ({1d3}*10) gp./job level) &
 [|apiece|apiece|apiece|total] and [@MageSpecialPay]
12-46: \n <b>Pay</b>: Average ({1d3}*100) gp.job/level) &
 [|apiece|apiece|apiece|total]
47-77: \n <b>Pay</b>: Average ({1d3}*100) gp.job/level) &
 [|apiece|apiece|apiece|total] and [@MageSpecialPay]
78-87: \n <b>Pay</b>: High (500 gp. job/level) &
 [|apiece|apiece|apiece|apiece|total]
88-96: \n <b>Pay</b>: High (500 gp. job/level) &
 [|apiece|apiece|apiece|apiece|total] and [@MageSpecialPay]
97-98: \n <b>Pay</b>: Munificent (1000 gp. job/level) &
 [|apiece|apiece|apiece|apiece|apiece|total]
99: \n <b>Pay</b>: Munificent (1000 gp. job/level) [|apiece|apiece|apiece|apiece|apiece|total] [@MageSpecialPay]
100: \n <b>Pay</b>: Munificent (1000 gp. job/level) &
 [|apiece|apiece|apiece|apiece|apiece|total] and [!2 MageSpecialPay]

Table:MageSpecialConditions
Type:Lookup
Roll: 1d100
01-85: \z
86: \n <b>Rider</b>: Mage must have full share
87: \n <b>Rider</b>: Mage must have half share
88: \n <b>Rider</b>: Mage must have half of any gains
89-91:\n <b>Rider</b>: Mage gets choice of item
92:\n <b>Rider</b>: Mage gets first refusal of choice of item
93-94:\n <b>Rider</b>: Party must surrender items
95:\n <b>Rider</b>: Party must surrender all gains
96-97:\n <b>Rider</b>: Party must surrender potions
98-99: \n <b>Rider</b> Party must surrender scrolls
100:\n <b>Rider</b>: Party must surrender gems

